p2
VDakshinayan comes to town
p3
sVnews
p4
VAfter the All India Barkha Ritu Festival held in the Capital this past July, it is now the turn of Dakshinayan, touted to be a grand Carnatic music festival.The festival is being organised at the FICCI auditorium for this Saturday. Dakshinayan received an enthusiastic response and spectacular success in Mumbai for the last two years as it featured some of the most popular and respected figures in Carnatic music like vocalistsM. Balamurali Krishna, Bombay Jayashri, Hyderabad sisters and K.J. Yesudas; Umalaypuram K. Sivaraman (mridangam); Ganesh Kumaresh (violin duet), T. Jayasankar (nadaswaram) and R. Jayanthi (veena).The Delhi programme will feature Bombay Jayashri (vocal), Vidwan Vikku Vinayakram (ghatam ensemble) and Vidwan U. Srinivas and U.Rajesh (mandolin).The programme is being organised by the Mumbai-based Banyan Tree Events, which since its inception over a decade ago, specialises in conceiving and presenting the best of unique, off beat, creative concepts. World class presentations of various traditional Indian performing arts through concerts that feature the best of musical geniuses from across the country is Banyan's forte. The company has been catering to the connoisseurs of 12 cities including all the metros.Bottom Template Starts
